editorialSummary.text: Brick-walled brasserie with an intimate feel serving updated French dishes and craft cocktails.

originalText.text: Saw this place and had to try it, it looks so beautiful inside and out. The food was pretty good too. Highly recommend the lobster gratin, roasted carrots and croquettes. The service was good, they didn’t have the bottle of wine we ordered off the menu which was a bummer. Definitely a good place, would come back and try other menu items.

originalText.text:
Went for a date night with my wife and we thoroughly enjoyed the whole experience. We made a reservation but it wasn’t super busy for a Friday night.

The drinks were delicious, really good espresso martinis including a bourbon-based version.

Food:
- tuna carpaccio: on par with expectations, fresh, tasty, recommend.
- beef tartare: this dish in general isn’t my favorite, but my wife who enjoys it said it was
top-tier.
- mezze: pretty good, it was more unique than mezze at Mediterranean places, not my favorite but not bad.
- croquettes: DELICIOUS, my favorite dish of the night.
- shrimp ceviche: also very good, highly recommend
- burger: they actually cooked it properly when we requested rare which has not been happening for us recently at other restaurants. Burger was very good and we were glad we got it.

My wife and I split everything which is what I would recommend so you can taste a little bit of everything. Our waiter was very attentive, we always had water (I tend to drink a lot of it), they timed the serving really well for us splitting the dishes.

Highly recommend this place. Great for a date night with a really nice vibe and well chosen decor.

originalText.text:
The main course was subpar and below expectations. They were out of two cocktails on a busy Thursday night. The service was also inconsistent. I made a reservation in the chandelier room, only to find out it’s closed for the day when I showed up.

One positive - the mezze appetizer was great.

We spent $200+ for a dinner for two. Your money could be spent better elsewhere with better service.

Overall, I would not recommend.

originalText.text:
Visited this restaurant last night and it was amazing. From the food, to the ambiance, it was absolutely perfect.
It’s a great date night spot. I ordered the lamb and it was cooked just right.
The cocktails were on point.
The service and staff were well versed and made excellent suggestions. Even had the opportunity to meet the owner who was very nice and welcoming.
As a native New Yorker I can definitely recommend Saint Restaurant Bar & Speakeasy as one of New York’s must visit restaurants.
Kudos to the owner and entire team for creating such an amazing experience.
Can’t wait to go back.
